# 47Chat Multi-Agent Orchestrator AI - Cursor Rules
# Advanced AI agent orchestration system with FastAPI backend and Streamlit frontend

## Project Context
You are working on 47Chat, a sophisticated multi-agent AI orchestration platform that coordinates specialized AI agents (alters) through structured discussions and workflows. The system uses FastAPI backend, Streamlit frontend, Ollama for local LLM integration, and FAISS for RAG capabilities.

## Code Style & Standards

### Python (FastAPI Backend)
- Use Python 3.11+ features and type hints extensively
- Follow PEP 8 with 88 character line limit (Black formatter)
- Use Pydantic v2 for data validation and serialization
- Implement proper async/await patterns for all I/O operations
- Use dependency injection for database connections and services
- Add comprehensive docstrings using Google style
- Implement proper error handling with custom exception classes

### FastAPI Specific
- Use APIRouter for modular route organization
- Implement proper HTTP status codes and response models
- Add OpenAPI documentation with examples
- Use Depends() for dependency injection
- Implement proper CORS configuration
- Add request/response logging middleware
- Use background tasks for long-running operations

### Agent Orchestration Patterns
- Implement clear separation between orchestrator logic and agent implementations
- Use factory patterns for agent creation and selection
- Implement proper state management for multi-turn conversations
- Add comprehensive logging for agent interactions and decisions
- Use structured data formats (JSON/Pydantic) for agent communication
- Implement proper timeout and retry mechanisms for agent calls

### LLM Integration
- Abstract LLM providers behind consistent interfaces
- Implement proper token counting and cost tracking
- Add comprehensive error handling for API failures
- Use connection pooling for external API calls
- Implement proper prompt templates and validation
- Add support for streaming responses where applicable

## Architecture Patterns

### Multi-Agent System Design
- Keep agents stateless where possible
- Use event-driven architecture for agent communication
- Implement proper agent lifecycle management
- Add comprehensive agent performance metrics
- Use factory patterns for dynamic agent creation
- Implement proper agent selection algorithms based on task analysis

### RAG Implementation
- Use FAISS for vector storage with proper indexing strategies
- Implement chunking strategies optimized for technical documentation
- Add proper document preprocessing and cleaning
- Use embedding models consistent with retrieval requirements
- Implement proper relevance scoring and ranking
- Add support for multiple document types and formats

### Security & Error Handling
- Sanitize all user inputs, especially for agent prompts
- Implement rate limiting on all API endpoints
- Add proper authentication and authorization layers
- Use environment variables for all sensitive configuration
- Implement comprehensive audit logging
- Add proper input validation for all agent parameters

## File Organization

### Backend Structure
backend/
├── orchestrator/ # Core orchestration logic
│ ├── agents/ # Agent implementations
│ ├── workflows/ # Workflow definitions
│ ├── utils/ # Shared utilities
│ └── tests/ # Unit and integration tests
├── api/ # FastAPI routes and models
├── core/ # Core business logic
└── config/ # Configuration management

text

### Code Quality Requirements
- All functions must have type hints and docstrings
- Minimum 80% test coverage for core orchestration logic
- Use pytest for testing with proper fixtures
- Implement property-based testing for agent selection logic
- Add integration tests for complete agent workflows
- Use mypy for static type checking

