text

### Error Handling
Comprehensive error handling for agent operations
class AgentExecutionError(Exception):
def init(self, agent_id: str, error_details: str):
self.agent_id = agent_id
self.error_details = error_details
super().init(f"Agent {agent_id} failed: {error_details}")

text

## Performance & Optimization

### Async Operations
- Use asyncio for all I/O bound operations
- Implement proper connection pooling for external APIs
- Use async context managers for resource management
- Implement proper backpressure handling for agent queues

### Caching Strategy
- Cache agent responses where appropriate
- Implement proper cache invalidation strategies
- Use Redis for distributed caching if scaling beyond single instance
- Cache embedding computations for RAG operations

### Monitoring & Observability
- Add comprehensive metrics for agent performance
- Implement proper logging with structured formats
- Track token usage and costs across all LLM providers
- Monitor agent selection accuracy and user satisfaction

## Dependencies & Libraries

### Core Dependencies
- fastapi[all] >= 0.104.0
- streamlit >= 1.28.0
- ollama >= 0.1.0
- faiss-cpu >= 1.7.4
- pydantic >= 2.5.0
- asyncio-mqtt for agent communication
- prometheus-client for metrics

### Development Dependencies
- pytest >= 7.4.0
- pytest-asyncio >= 0.21.0
- black >= 23.0.0
- mypy >= 1.7.0
- ruff >= 0.1.0

## Security Considerations

### Input Validation
- Validate all agent parameters and prompts
- Implement proper schema validation for API requests
- Sanitize user inputs to prevent prompt injection
- Add rate limiting per user/session

### API Security
- Use proper HTTPS in production
- Implement API key management for external services
- Add CORS configuration appropriate for deployment
- Use secure session management for multi-turn conversations

## Documentation Requirements
- All agent implementations must include usage examples
- API endpoints must have comprehensive OpenAPI documentation
- Include architecture diagrams for complex orchestration flows
- Maintain up-to-date README with setup and deployment instructions

## Testing Strategy
- Unit tests for all agent selection logic
- Integration tests for complete orchestration workflows
- Performance tests for agent coordination under load
- Security tests for input validation and sanitization